<h2><a name="union" id="union">union</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="kw4">union</span> union<span class="sy0">-</span>name <span class="br0">&#123;</span>
    public<span class="sy0">-</span>members<span class="sy0">-</span>list;
    private<span class="sy0">:</span>
    private<span class="sy0">-</span>members<span class="sy0">-</span>list;
    <span class="br0">&#125;</span> object<span class="sy0">-</span>list;</pre>
<p>

A union is like a class, except that all members of a union share the same
memory location and are by default public rather than private. For example:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">     <span class="kw4">union</span> Data <span class="br0">&#123;</span>
       <span class="kw4">int</span> i;
       <span class="kw4">char</span> c;
     <span class="br0">&#125;</span>;</pre>
<p>
Related Topics: <a href="class" class="wikilink1" title="keywords:class">class</a>, <a href="struct" class="wikilink1" title="keywords:struct">struct</a>
</p>

